  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nTried to cross build from a Macbook Pro to amd64. Builder got Killed (OOM? I have 64GB RAM).\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\n`srtable` branch\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\n```\r\n% docker buildx build --platform linux/amd64\r\n\r\n[...]\r\n\r\n#0 174.4    Compiling cfg-if v1.0.0\r\n#0 174.7 <jemalloc>: MADV_DONTNEED does not work (memset will be used instead)\r\n#0 174.7 <jemalloc>: (This is the expected behaviour if you are running under QEMU)\r\n#0 174.7 <jemalloc>: MADV_DONTNEED does not work (memset will be used instead)\r\n#0 174.7 <jemalloc>: (This is the expected behaviour if you are running under QEMU)\r\n#0 174.8 <jemalloc>: MADV_DONTNEED does not work (memset will be used instead)\r\n#0 174.8 <jemalloc>: (This is the expected behaviour if you are running under QEMU)\r\n#0 174.8 <jemalloc>: MADV_DONTNEED does not work (memset will be used instead)\r\n#0 174.8 <jemalloc>: (This is the expected behaviour if you are running under QEMU)\r\n#0 174.9 <jemalloc>: MADV_DONTNEED does not work (memset will be used instead)\r\n#0 174.9 <jemalloc>: (This is the expected behaviour if you are running under QEMU)\r\n#0 174.9 <jemalloc>: MADV_DONTNEED does not work (memset will be used instead)\r\n#0 174.9 <jemalloc>: (This is the expected behaviour if you are running under QEMU)\r\n#0 175.3    Compiling autocfg v1.1.0\r\n#0 175.6 <jemalloc>: MADV_DONTNEED does not work (memset will be used instead)\r\n#0 175.6 <jemalloc>: (This is the expected behaviour if you are running under QEMU)\r\n#0 176.5    Compiling syn v1.0.109\r\n#0 176.9 <jemalloc>: MADV_DONTNEED does not work (memset will be used instead)\r\n#0 176.9 <jemalloc>: (This is the expected behaviour if you are running under QEMU)\r\n#0 179.8 Killed\r\n#0 179.8 make: *** [Makefile:48: install] Error 137\r\n------\r\nERROR: failed to solve: executor failed running [/bin/sh -c cd lighthouse && make]: exit code: 2\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nBuild succeeds\r\n",
